y also makes it possible for them to be transformed by friendship. Friendship, then, is possible and good for those who love precisely that they can never wholly know the friend. Friendship is a profound, mutual self-giving that highlights the irreplaceability of each person, fundamentally shapes the self, and is one of the greatest joys of human existence.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aFriendship. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Ethics. 4aPhilosophy : Phenomenology. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Theology. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Deconstruction.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2023z978311149193640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849517040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438495170423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438495170/original  a978-3-11-149193-6  SUNY Press eBook Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles